HEADWORD: Thermophore
<hw>Ther"mo*phore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thermo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ -bearing, fr. <grk>fe`rein</grk> to
bear.]</ety> <def>An apparatus for conveying heat, as a case containing
material which retains its heat for a considerable period.</def>⟦br⟧
